# Code Style Rules

## 1. No alignment spaces

Use a single space only. Do **not** add extra spaces to push symbols into columns — in parameter lists, field declarations, object initialisers, expression-body members (`=>`), switch expression arms, and assignments.

**Wrong:**
```csharp
Guid?   ClientId       = null,
bool    HasReturn      = false,
_filterEntity     = null;
Id        = Guid.NewGuid(),
```

**Correct:**
```csharp
Guid? ClientId = null,
bool HasReturn = false,
_filterEntity = null;
Id = Guid.NewGuid(),
```

---

## 2. Blank line between properties in models

Each property in a class or record must be separated from the next by a blank line.

**Wrong:**
```csharp
public int Created { get; set; }
public int Updated { get; set; }
```

**Correct:**
```csharp
public int Created { get; set; }

public int Updated { get; set; }
```

---

## 3. No separator comments

Do **not** use decorative separator comments (`// ── ... ────`). Use a blank line to visually group members.

---

## 4. Exactly one blank line between methods

No more than one blank line between methods.

---

## 5. One class per file

Each `.cs` file must contain exactly one top-level type.

---

## 6. All models in `StudioB2B.Shared`

All DTO and model classes go in `StudioB2B.Shared`. Every file in that project declares `namespace StudioB2B.Shared;` regardless of subdirectory.

---

## 7. Layered architecture

```
UI Layer  (Blazor .razor, Controllers)
    ↓  @inject / constructor — interfaces only
Service Layer  (Infrastructure/Services/)
    ↓  uses extension-methods
Feature Layer  (Infrastructure/Features/)
    ↓  EF Core
Database
```

- `.razor` files and controllers must **never** inject `ITenantDbContextFactory` or `IMapper` directly.
- All database work goes through the Service layer.

---

## 8. No unnecessary `using` directives and `@inject` declarations

### C# files

Only add `using` directives for namespaces **actually referenced** in the file.

**Wrong:**
```csharp
using System.Net.Http;           // not used
using Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore; // not used
```

**Correct:** omit any using not referenced in the file.

### Razor files — `@using`

`Components/_Imports.razor` already imports these globally — **never repeat them** in individual `.razor` files:

- `Radzen`
- `Radzen.Blazor`
- `StudioB2B.Domain.Constants`
- `StudioB2B.Web.Services`
- `StudioB2B.Web.Components.Common`
- `StudioB2B.Shared`
- `Microsoft.AspNetCore.Authorization`
- `Microsoft.AspNetCore.Components.Authorization`
- (and all other namespaces in `_Imports.razor`)

**Wrong:**
```razor
@using Radzen
@using StudioB2B.Domain.Constants
@using StudioB2B.Shared
```

**Correct:** omit — already globally available.

### Razor files — `@inject`

Only inject services that are **actually called** in the component's markup or `@code` block.

**Wrong:**
```razor
@inject DialogService DialogService         @* never called *@
@inject NavigationManager Navigation        @* never called *@
```

**Correct:** include only injections the component actually uses.

---

## 9. Service pattern for new modules

**Step 1** — Interface `StudioB2B.Infrastructure/Interfaces/I[Module]Service.cs`
**Step 2** — Implementation `StudioB2B.Infrastructure/Services/[Module]Service.cs`
**Step 3** — Register in `DependencyInjection.cs`: `services.AddScoped<I[Module]Service, [Module]Service>();`
**Step 4** — Controller/Razor: inject the interface, never `ITenantDbContextFactory` or `IMapper` directly.

---

## 10. Role & Permission System — always use `nameof`

**Wrong:**
```csharp
@attribute [Authorize(Roles = "OrdersView")]
IsInRole("UsersManage")
```

**Correct:**
```csharp
@attribute [Authorize(Roles = nameof(PageEnum.OrdersView))]
IsInRole(nameof(FunctionEnum.UsersManage))
```

`"Admin"` is always a plain string literal — it is not in any enum.

Checklist for new page:
- `PageEnum` — new value with `[Description]`
- `NavService.cs` — `NavItem` with `Role = nameof(PageEnum.*)`
- `.razor` — `@attribute [Authorize(Roles = nameof(PageEnum.*))]`

Checklist for new function:
- `FunctionEnum` — new value with `[Description]`
- `TenantDatabaseInitializer.cs → FunctionPageMap` — new entry
- Razor — `<AuthorizeView Roles="@nameof(FunctionEnum.*)">` / `IsInRole(nameof(FunctionEnum.*))`

Checklist for new grid column:
- `PageColumnEnum` — new value with `[Description]`
- `TenantDatabaseInitializer.cs → ColumnPageMap` — new entry
- Razor — `Visible="@Col(nameof(PageColumnEnum.*))"`

